: "Pension Plans", "bbox": [183.3, 1169.4, 303.2, 1190.2]}, {"text": "Substantially all regular employees in North America and the U.K. are covered by defined benefit pension", "bbox": [204.2, 1208.7, 1112.4, 1229.5]}, {"text": "plans (the “Principal Plans”) and/or defined contribution retirement plans. Certain other subsidiaries have defined", "bbox": [162.5, 1233.7, 1112.4, 1254.5]}, {"text": "benefit pension plans or, in certain countries, termination pay plans covering substantially all regular employees.", "bbox": [162.5, 1258.7, 1112.3, 1279.5]}, {"text": "The funding policy for the qualified defined benefit plans in North America and the defined benefit plans in the", "bbox": [162.5, 1283.7, 1112.4, 1304.5]}, {"text": "U.K. is to contribute assets equal in amount to the higher of the accumulated benefit obligation (“ABO”) or", "bbox": [162.5, 1308.7, 1112.5, 1329.5]}, {"text": "regulatory minimum requirements. Subject to regulatory requirements and tax deductibility limits, any funding", "bbox": [162.5, 1333.7, 1112.4, 1354.5]}, {"text": "shortfall will be eliminated over a reasonable number of years. Nonqualified U.S. plans providing pension", "bbox": [162.5, 1358.7, 1112.4, 1379.5]}, {"text": "benefits in excess of limitations imposed by the U.S. income tax code are not funded. Funding for the remaining", "bbox": [162.5, 1383.7, 1112.3, 1404.5]}, {"text": "defined benefit plans outside the U.S. is based on legal requirements, tax considerations, investment", "bbox": [162.5, 1408.7, 1112.3, 1429.5]}, {"text": "opportunities, and customary business practices in such countries.", "bbox": [162.5, 1433.7, 712.5, 1454.5]}, {"text": "58", "bbox": [627.1, 1484.1, 647.9, 1504.9]}]}